{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 200°C and line a baking tray with baking paper.","Place quinoa and chia seeds in mixing bowl then grind <nobr>30 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides and lid of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add water, sesame seeds and salt then mix <nobr>6 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Finish stirring by hand with spatula.","Form into walnut-sized balls. Lay balls between 2 sheets of cling film then, roll out each to a thickness of 1-2 mm. Use a pastry cutter (Ø 8 cm) to cut out circles. Arrange on prepared baking tray.","Bake for 5 minutes (200°C). Repeat with remaining dough, re-rolling any trimmings. Allow to cool before serving or store in an airtight container until needed."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["100 g quinoa","50 g chia seeds","70 g water","10 g sesame seeds","¼ tsp fine sea salt"]}],"id":"r128725","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-aqiWinrnd3Q\/XZaqqx-q2_I\/AAAAAAAAhfc\/Z2G5YyJC64YX2DcYCbNrSblVlc0FzpL8wCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_iBWQmEdaBdcmaOPi.png","title":"Quinoa and Chia Chips","publishedAt":"2017-01-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"0.65 g","fat":"0.44 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"2.09 g","calories":"62 kJ \/ 15 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray and baking paper, airtight container, cling film, rolling pin, round pastry cutter (Ø 8 cm), oven","hintsAndTricks":["For curved chips, try using a baguette tray instead of a flat baking tray to bake the chips.","Serve with dips."],"basicInfo":["easy","45m","45m","24 pieces"]}